<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,633,984]" pageId="39" pageNumber="549">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,327,633,659]" pageId="39" pageNumber="549">Nomenclature.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Ahmad &amp; Afzal" authorityYear="1979" box="[460,651,634,659]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Riazocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis box="[460,651,634,659]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="549">Riazocoris nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with explicitly given authorship of Ahmad and Afzal first appeared in morphological paper devoted to description of its internal organs by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ahmad, I. &amp; Afzal, M. &amp; Siddiqui, M. I." box="[955,1186,669,695]" pageId="39" pageNumber="549" pagination="161 - 165" refId="ref27925" refString="Ahmad, I., Afzal, M. &amp; Siddiqui, M. I. (1977) Aspects of morphology of Riazocoris nigra Ahmad and Afzal (Pentatominae: Caystrini) with phylogenetic considerations. Pakistan Journal of Zoology, 9 (2), 161 - 165." type="journal article" year="1977">
Ahmad 
<emphasis box="[1045,1102,669,695]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="549">et al.</emphasis>
(1977)
</bibRefCitation>
, which is sufficient to make it available from that publication. The intended original description appeared later in 
<bibRefCitation author="Ahmad, I. &amp; Afzal, M." pageId="39" pageNumber="549" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref27835" refString="Ahmad, I. &amp; Afzal, M. (1979) Resurrection of the tribe Caystrini Stal (Heteroptera, Pentatomidae, Pentatominae) with description of two new genera from Oriental region. Annotationes Zoologicae et Botanicae, 133, 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="1979">Ahmad &amp; Afzal (1979: 4)</bibRefCitation>
. The fact that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ahmad &amp; Afzal" authorityYear="1979" box="[344,464,742,767]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Riazocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[344,464,742,767]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="549">Riazocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been combined with an unavailable generic name in 
<bibRefCitation author="Ahmad, I. &amp; Afzal, M. &amp; Siddiqui, M. I." box="[1121,1353,741,767]" pageId="39" pageNumber="549" pagination="161 - 165" refId="ref27925" refString="Ahmad, I., Afzal, M. &amp; Siddiqui, M. I. (1977) Aspects of morphology of Riazocoris nigra Ahmad and Afzal (Pentatominae: Caystrini) with phylogenetic considerations. Pakistan Journal of Zoology, 9 (2), 161 - 165." type="journal article" year="1977">
Ahmad 
<emphasis box="[1212,1270,741,767]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="549">et al.</emphasis>
(1977)
</bibRefCitation>
has no effect on its availability (see 
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[469,601,777,803]" pageId="39" pageNumber="549" refId="ref31005" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 4 th Edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 11.9.3.1). There is no mention of type material in 
<bibRefCitation author="Ahmad, I. &amp; Afzal, M. &amp; Siddiqui, M. I." box="[1205,1432,777,803]" pageId="39" pageNumber="549" pagination="161 - 165" refId="ref27925" refString="Ahmad, I., Afzal, M. &amp; Siddiqui, M. I. (1977) Aspects of morphology of Riazocoris nigra Ahmad and Afzal (Pentatominae: Caystrini) with phylogenetic considerations. Pakistan Journal of Zoology, 9 (2), 161 - 165." type="journal article" year="1977">
Ahmad 
<emphasis box="[1294,1349,777,803]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="549">et al.</emphasis>
(1977)
</bibRefCitation>
. As 
<typeStatus box="[192,290,813,839]" pageId="39" pageNumber="549">holotype</typeStatus>
is defined as ‘the single specimen upon which a new nominal species-group taxon is based in the original publication’ (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[394,529,849,875]" pageId="39" pageNumber="549" refId="ref31005" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 4 th Edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 73.1), the subsequently designated ‘holotype’ by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ahmad, I. &amp; Afzal, M." box="[1144,1436,849,876]" pageId="39" pageNumber="549" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref27835" refString="Ahmad, I. &amp; Afzal, M. (1979) Resurrection of the tribe Caystrini Stal (Heteroptera, Pentatomidae, Pentatominae) with description of two new genera from Oriental region. Annotationes Zoologicae et Botanicae, 133, 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="1979">Ahmad &amp; Afzal (1979: 7)</bibRefCitation>
must be considered the 
<typeStatus box="[418,521,885,911]" pageId="39" pageNumber="549">lectotype</typeStatus>
according to 
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[675,818,885,911]" pageId="39" pageNumber="549" refId="ref31005" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 4 th Edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN (1999</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 74.5). As the generic names ending with - 
<emphasis box="[1351,1407,886,911]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="549">coris</emphasis>
(a Latinized Greek noun meaning true bug) are masculines, the gender agreement of the species name is corrected as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ahmad &amp; Afzal" authorityYear="1977" box="[151,241,958,983]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Riazocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niger">
<emphasis box="[151,241,958,983]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="549">R. niger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to 
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[395,536,957,983]" pageId="39" pageNumber="549" refId="ref31005" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 4 th Edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN (1999</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 31.2).
</paragraph>
